BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:W7LKDokG_g6TmxKQ2-C9R
SUMMARY:Learn at LANGSTON: Healing Drum Workshop
DTSTAMP:20260330T060600Z
DTSTART:20260331T004500Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Community\,Ethnic/Cultural\,Music\,Training-Cla ss
	es/Workshops\n\nNeighborhoods: Central Area/Squire Park\n\nSponsoring Orga
	nization: LANGSTON\n\nContact: Jahi McGhee\n\nContact Phone: 2066844758\n\
	nContact Email: langston.institute@seattle.gov\n\nAudience: All\n\nPre-Reg
	ister: Yes\n\nCost: Free\n\nLink: https://www.langstonseattle.org/programs
	/healing-drum-workshop/\n\nDrums are provided. All ages. No experience nec
	essary.\n\nThe Hawk Foundation for Research and Education in African Cultu
	re brings master drummers t o LANGSTON to engage in a well-researched peda
	gogy of community healing through African drumming.\n\nThe Hawk Foundation
	 is a Washington-based drum and education organization that utilizes West 
	African and African American music to promote education\, team bonding\, o
	rganizational de velopment\, and research-based therapy. Through history\,
	 Yoruba stories and classic drum rhythms\, this class has reconnected stud
	ents to the drum\, the past\, and themselves.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-healing-drum-workshop/18448016/2026
	-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-healing
	-drum-workshop/18448016/2026-03-30T00
LOCATION:Langston Hughes Performing Arts Institute\, 104 17th Avenue South 
	West Room\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT45M
END:VEVENT
