BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xlQy4jeIAZsOc2sGFLJ8V
SUMMARY:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light
DTSTAMP:20260330T060601Z
DTSTART:20260412T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light invites you to become par
	t of the art. Agha\, a Pakistani American artist\, animates spaces with he
	r large-scale sculptural installations. Suspended from the ceiling\, Agha’
	s steel cubes are laser-cut with intricate designs that project geometric 
	shadows onto the visitor. She draws on both the light and dark of her own 
	life\, using South Asian art practices to convey the gender discrimination
	 she faced growing up as a young girl in Pakistan. An in-depth exploration
	 of Islamic architecture\, art\, and identity\, this is the first solo exh
	ibition of a Pakistani American artist in SAM’s 90-year history. Agha is c
	arving a name out for herself in the art world—visit the Seattle Asian Art
	 Museum for an immersive and illuminating experience.\n\nhttps://seatoday.
	6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geometry-of-light/16795597
	/2026-04-12T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geomet
	ry-of-light/16795597/2026-04-12T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:GYli4hrUU9WpU62Y10kvU
SUMMARY:Youth Soapstone Carving Workshops At Best of the Northwest Art Show
DTSTAMP:20260330T060601Z
DTSTART:20260412T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Northwest Stone Sculptors Association \\(NWSSA\\) is excite
	d to offer Youth Soapstone Carving Workshops during the Northwest Art Alli
	ance Best of the Northwest Spring Show on April 11th & 12th at Magnuson Pa
	rk Hangar 30.\n\nYouth can participate an up-close\, hands-on experience w
	ith creativity by learning to carve their own soapstone animal figurine. A
	rtist instructors from the Northwest Stone Sculptors Association will guid
	e youth participants Ages 7 – 17 through the process of shaping this beaut
	iful\, natural material into a figurine to take home. These workshops are 
	designed to promote fine motor skills\, 3D spatial reasoning\, and artisti
	c confidence. The soapstone and all necessary kid-safe tools and water to 
	minimize dust will be provided.\n\nThe youth workshops are Free with admis
